58 I answered him: “Ciacco, your sorrow
59 weighs on me so much, that it invites me to weep;
60 but tell me, if you know, to what will come

61 the citizens of the departed city;
62 if any are just; and tell me the reason
63 for which such discord has assaulted it.”

73 Just are two, and they are not understood by you;
74 pride, envy and avarice are
75 the three sparks that have their hearts ignited.

85 And he: “They are among the blackest souls;
86 different faults weigh them down to the bottom:
87 if you descend so much, there you will be able to see them.”

91 The straight eyes he turned then in wicked ones;
92 he looked at me a little and then bent the head:
93 he fell with it in a manner of the other blind ones.

